    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
      <subfield code="a">We use the Bose-Hubbard model with an effective infinite-range interaction to describe the correlated lattice bosons in an optical cavity. We study both static and spectral properties of such system within the bosonic dynamical mean-field theory, which is the state-of-the-art method for strongly correlated bosonic systems. Both similarities and differences are found and discussed between our results and those obtained within different theoretical methods and experiment.</subfield>
      <subfield code="9">APS</subfield>
    </datafield>
